RESPONSIBILITIES:
Define and establish automation strategy and processes. Take ownership and responsibility for the design and development of all aspects of automated testing along with creation, integration, execution, and maintenance of automated scripts. Estimate, prioritize, plan, and coordinate all testing activities.

REQUIREMENTS:
Bachelor’s degree or equivalent in Computer Science, Electronic Engineering or related field.

5 years of progressive experience in the job offered defined as Quality Engineering.

Work experience to include:
1. 3 years of experience in testing web-based applications;
2. 2 years of experience with at least two of the following: HTML, XHTML, CSS, JavaScript, JQuery, AJAX, or JSON testing;
3. experience in Selenium IDE;
4. writing Java based automation tests using Selenium WebDriver;
5. performing white-box and black-box testing;
6. writing test and load automation frameworks;
7. experience using any one of the following repositories for check-in codes for automation: BitBucket, Tortoise SVN or Git;
8. testing cross browser compatibility and layout issues;
9. developing test cases for rapid prototypes and rapidly iterating designs;
10. testing using Agile development methodologies; and
11. writing SQL commands for querying data for validation.


Any and all experience may be gained currently.
Pursuant to the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance, we will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records.

Individuals interested in applying for the position may mail a resume to:
TrustArc Inc, HR Dept., Job #MD-1003, 835 Market Street, Suite 800, San Francisco, CA 94103

This position is eligible for employee referral pursuant to company guidelines.
